1
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,480
Marry me.

2
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,960
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,800
Is Puna really my child?

4
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:40,240
Death is so close to us.

5
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:43,200
I don't want to hide this anymore.

6
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,880
It's an old-style videotape.

7
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,840
I must have dropped it at your shop.

8
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,720
I didn't see it.

9
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,360
Why did you lie about the tape?

10
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:55,080
This is from Chaiya. It's a GPS tracker.

11
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:57,520
<i>Get someone to deal with Boss Noo.</i>

12
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,000
I'll meet you at the safe house.

13
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,920
The GPS has moved away
from Singha's house.

14
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,880
On it, buddy.

15
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:08,960
Clear the area!

16
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,680
-You two, follow me.
-Yes, sir.

17
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,640
Go!

18
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,560
-Don't struggle!
-Let go!

19
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:23,360
-Hey!
-Stay still!

20
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,800
Corporal Chom, put on the handcuffs.

21
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,200
Come here.

22
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,920
Stay still. Don't fight.

23
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,360
Don't move.

24
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:31,920
What are we doing with Kitti?

25
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,760
If we take him to the station,

26
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,600
he'll probably be released.

27
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:39,160
If we call the Crime Suppression Division,
they might catch on.

28
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,640
Then stick to the plan.

29
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,040
Keep Kitti locked up here for now.

30
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,680
-Let me go!
-Stay still!

31
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:50,480
Just you wait! If I get out,

32
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,920
I'll get back at all of you!

33
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,800
Let me warn you!

34
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,680
Things have gone this far.
If you don't come to your senses,

35
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:01,760
you're in big trouble.
With the evidence I have,

36
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:06,880
you're one of the drug traffickers,
and the penalty is death.

37
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,800
Work with us.

38
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:15,800
If you cooperate or provide
useful information to catch the suspects,

39
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:18,120
you'll get some leniency,
at least a little.

40
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,440
Think carefully.

41
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,000
Your ship is sinking.

42
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,840
If you don't grab the lifeline,

43
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,880
you'll drown.

44
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,040
What the heck?

45
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:59,440
-How many are dead?
-Almost all of them.

46
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,760
-Did any of them follow us?
-No, sir.

47
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:05,960
I tried calling Kitti,
but his phone's off!

48
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:09,200
I think Mr. Kitti's hiding for now.

49
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,880
Give it time. He'll get back to us.

50
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:15,200
I've already informed
Superintendent Samuejai.

51
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,400
Go tell Chart

52
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:21,520
to keep an eye on Boss Noo's gang.
Report immediately if anything happens.

53
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,760
Yes, Boss.

54
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,720
Kitti!

55
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,880
You two are safe, right?

56
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:42,880
Yes.

57
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:45,320
-We're safe.
-Let's go. Follow me.

58
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,840
Okay.

59
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,080
Let's go.

60
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,920
This way.

61
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,160
Wait.

62
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,680
Thank you for helping us.

63
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,040
But where are you taking us?

64
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:09,480
From here, Kamnan Pong
will take you both to a safe place.

65
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,880
A safe place?

66
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,160
-But we're worried about Puna.
-Yes.

67
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,640
By the honor of the Thai police,

68
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:22,920
I promise I will protect Puna
with my life.

69
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,200
Police?

70
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,200
You're a police officer?

71
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:35,320
Let's go quickly. This way. Follow me.

72
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,480
You know who the 14K gang is, right?

73
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:50,480
The origin of this mafia is in Hong Kong.

74
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,760
They were suppressed there,

75
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,000
so they scattered across other countries.

76
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:59,200
Thailand is one of the countries
they infiltrated.

77
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:04,000
They run legitimate companies as a front,
but in reality, they deal drugs,

78
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,280
launder money, and run call center gangs.

79
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:11,240
Actually, Boss Noo
was just one of their delivery men.

80
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,160
But when Singha betrayed him,

81
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,800
he went to the 14K gang
for help to get revenge.

82
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,360
Right now, Singha's facing a huge battle.

83
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,520
Yes. He's dealing with both the drug case

84
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:27,080
and an old case that's still active.

85
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,360
What case?

86
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:38,159
The murder of Ms. Onanong,
Mr. Phupha, and Ms. Namthip.

87
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,840
On Puna's wedding day,

88
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:43,600
the statute for this case will expire.

89
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,760
Therefore,

90
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:48,680
we have to get everything done
by that day.

91
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:53,720
Don't worry about the paperwork.
It's ready. We just need to capture them.

92
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,520
-Hello.
-Is this Kamnan Pong's number?

93
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,880
Who's this?

94
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:10,080
This is Village Head Prueng.

95
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,680
Village Head Prueng?

96
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,240
Wait. Where are you going?

97
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,760
It's the wedding day.
I'm here to take Puna for her makeup.

98
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:33,920
No, the boss didn't order this.

99
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,240
It's bridal makeup, not just event makeup.

100
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,600
It takes time.
If we don't go now, it'll be too late.

101
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,520
She's here, Teacher. Puna's here.

102
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,240
Puna!

103
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,880
I've scheduled the makeup artist.

104
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,600
Today, you have to be
the most beautiful bride.

105
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,720
Why's everyone here today?

106
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,680
It's nothing, Sonrak.

107
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,200
Today's your wedding.

108
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:10,680
There'll be lots of media and fans,

109
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,720
so I'm worried about the chaos.

110
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:16,520
That's why I've arranged people
to handle security.

111
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,080
Yes, Dad.

112
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:23,040
Chart, take Sonrak and Puna
to the wedding hall.

113
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,880
Keep them safe.
Make sure nothing goes wrong.

114
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,080
Yes, Boss.

115
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,720
-Let's go together, Teacher.
-Of course.

116
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,800
Let's go.

117
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,320
I'll excuse myself.

118
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,040
I know you're upset.

119
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,680
But what good will sulking do, man?

120
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:02,600
Who said I'm upset?

121
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:08,360
I knew it had to turn out this way.
I've been preparing myself.

122
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,800
No matter what, we finish this today.

123
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,880
That's the way, buddy.

124
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,120
Time to follow the plan.

125
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:29,840
Manat.

126
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:34,600
-Don't die.
-You too.

127
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,160
Are you done?

128
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:03,760
Yes, all done. I'll excuse myself now.

129
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:04,800
Thank you.

130
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,440
It's time. Let's go to the wedding.

131
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,360
Smile a little, my bride.

132
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:29,400
Don't force me.
I've already agreed to everything.

133
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,880
Puna, what's wrong?
Why are you saying that?

134
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:37,240
You don't look happy.

135
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,520
I can't say anything.

136
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,040
Let's just go.

137
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:54,160
Hey!

138
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,120
It's time to eat.

139
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:02,520
Hey, there's some good stuff here too!

140
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,520
-Help…
-Huh?

141
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,920
Help me unlock this.

142
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Oh right, I almost forgot. Unlock…

143
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:17,080
Hey! Are you crazy?
If I unlock you, you'll run!

144
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:20,560
You know, I'm not stupid.
I'll leave it right here.

145
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,480
It's here. Oh no, damn it!

146
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:26,640
-Let go! What are you doing?
-You!

147
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:27,560
Let go!

148
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,800
Hey! You bastard! Want a taste of this?

149
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:52,800
Oops, they are really with you.

150
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,200
Let's talk this through calmly.

151
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,200
This is it.

152
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,480
Kitti must be inside.

153
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,480
-Kitti!
-Whoa!

154
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,800
Go!

155
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,760
Hey.

156
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,920
Get down! Everyone, get down!

157
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,320
Wait! Don't shoot yet.

158
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,160
-Which unit are you from?
-Shut up!

159
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,720
Deputy Chief!

160
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,960
Follow me.

161
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:32,080
Where to, sir?

162
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,760
Don't say a word

163
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,440
if you don't want to die here.

164
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,480
Sir, you can't do this.

165
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:39,960
He's not resisting.

166
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,120
None of your business. Be quiet.

167
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:45,920
Deputy Chief.

168
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:48,200
If you're going to deal with me,

169
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,600
deal with me alone.

170
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,360
Captain Tom and the other police
aren't involved.

171
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,520
Please don't touch them.

172
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:02,080
Speak less, and they live.

173
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,160
-Take him!
-Move!

174
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,119
Hurry up!

175
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:31,480
Before you kill me to silence me,

176
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,280
may I ask you

177
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,160
one thing before I die?

178
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:37,960
What do you want?

179
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,040
Today's Puna's wedding.

180
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:02,640
I'm entrusting this to you.

181
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,520
Please give it to Puna.

182
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:12,000
Give her my blessings.

183
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,240
I hope she'll be happy.

184
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:18,360
In this life…

185
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,080
I can't restore justice
for her and her family.

186
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,960
If there's a next life…

187
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,280
I hope to meet her again.

188
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,240
I will remember her forever.

189
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,160
Have you ever heard people say

190
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,440
that the path to heaven is overgrown,

191
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,480
but the path to hell is clear?

192
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:12,680
You're an honest cop. I admire you.

193
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:16,960
I must apologize
for being such a lousy leader.

194
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:21,840
I've failed to endure hardship
as well as you.

195
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,280
May you die in peace.

196
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,320
Farewell.

197
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:37,760
Captain.

198
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:40,880
This can't happen.

199
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,840
Get in the car now.

200
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:58,000
No! You can't leave his body here!

201
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:01,080
You can't do this
to a good cop like Captain Chaiya!

202
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:04,200
I'll die if I must.
I couldn't stand it either.

203
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,400
What's the point of doing good

204
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:07,840
if it gets you shot like a stray dog?

205
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,960
Let me go! Let go!

206
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:18,600
Move!

207
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,760
-Chaiya!
-Captain Chaiya!

208
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:25,560
What are you waiting for? Go help him!

209
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,880
Corporal, go!

210
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,960
Thought you weren't gonna make it.

211
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,200
-Thanks a lot, Corporal.
-Yes.

212
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,000
-Move.
-Move!

213
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,520
-Take him!
-Yes.

214
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,760
Move!

215
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:54,640
Thank you, Deputy Chief,
for not interfering with this mission.

216
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:57,080
Why would I?

217
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:59,000
This mission is a secret assignment

218
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:02,040
I entrusted to you from the start.

219
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:06,840
I apologize for speaking poorly earlier,
both me and Corporal Chom.

220
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:10,360
You two are good cops. I won't be angry.

221
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:16,840
Captain, you must complete
this mission today.

222
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:20,920
If you fail to put Singha
and Kitti behind bars,

223
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,480
they'll come after you for sure.

224
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,280
Yes, sir.

225
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,240
These are the officers
I've assigned to support you.

226
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,400
I'll stay back and observe.

227
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:34,640
Go and eliminate them completely.

228
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,400
-Yes, sir.
-Yes.

229
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:52,600
Alright, get everything ready.
The event is about to start.

230
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,040
Praewa.

231
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,240
Is everything set? Anything missing?

232
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,440
Everything's fine.

233
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:04,400
But the presentation files might change.

234
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:07,640
Wait for Teacher Mueangphrai
to tell you which files to use.

235
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,800
Got it. I'll get going then.

236
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:15,840
Ms. Prae.

237
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,800
Oh, Teacher.

238
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,440
Maria hasn't arrived yet.

239
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:25,040
Don't worry, Teacher.
We still have a little time to wait.

240
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:27,880
I'll wait by the back door then.

241
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,320
Okay.

242
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:39,080
Thanks. See you inside.

243
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:41,600
Ice, you did a great job with the setup.

244
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,040
Thank you, Kamnan.

245
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:45,280
Hello! See you inside. See you in a bit.

246
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:47,720
-Mr. Singha is waiting over there.
-Alright.

247
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:50,240
-Hello, Kamnan. Thank you very much.
-Hello.

248
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:51,920
Hello, Kamnan.

249
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,000
Congratulations, Sonrak.

250
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,520
Thank you.

251
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:04,120
How are you? Feeling tired?

252
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,600
You don't look very cheerful.

253
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:09,400
Well, she's just tired
from all the preparations.

254
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:12,760
Hang in there.

255
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,840
It'll pass soon.

256
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:20,360
What was that, Kamnan?

257
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,560
Nothing.

258
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,840
Well, shall we take a group photo?

259
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,440
-Come on. Let's take a photo.
-Yes.

260
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,080
-May I?
-Go ahead.

261
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:29,240
Congratulations! Come on, everyone!

262
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,640
Camera to the left, please.
One, two, three.

263
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,200
Good.

264
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:43,800
-Come here. Bride and groom together.
-Thank you.

265
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,520
Excuse me, bride and groom,
give a little smile.

266
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:50,120
Smile.

267
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,760
Why are you hiding here?

268
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:01,280
There are so many guards.
I'm scared I'll get caught.

269
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,880
So what do we do next?

270
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:10,080
Stay here, Village Head.
Chaiya and Captain Tom are on their way.

271
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,520
What about me?

272
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,720
Come with me. Don't worry.

273
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,160
I'll protect you.

274
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:40,040
What's wrong? Why are you blushing?

275
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,600
Nothing! Just lead the way!

276
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:06,040
Welcome, distinguished guests!

277
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,600
I'm Praewa,

278
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:12,240
your host for the wedding
of Puna and Sonrak.

279
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:15,160
I'm delighted to have you here today.

280
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:22,600
Now, let's welcome our bride and groom

281
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:25,160
with the song "Please Consider".

282
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:28,400
Enjoy the performance!

283
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,680
<i>Take my heart</i>

284
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:48,920
<i>For your consideration</i>

285
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,600
<i>Check it out and see</i>

286
00:25:52,680 --> 00:25:56,640
<i>If my heart is new or old</i>

287
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:59,160
<i>Is it broken?</i>

288
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:02,160
<i>Is there any damage?</i>

289
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:05,640
<i>Or are there any cracks</i>

290
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:09,440
<i>Glued over to hide the truth?</i>

291
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:13,040
<i>The four chambers of my heart</i>

292
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,960
<i>Are still brand new</i>

293
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:19,800
<i>True and genuine, not fake or false</i>

294
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:23,280
<i>No tricks, no schemes</i>

295
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:26,640
<i>Only overflowing love</i>

296
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:30,040
<i>Filling every corner of my heart</i>

297
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:37,080
<i>I'm willing to give it to you</i>
<i>Please accept it and consider</i>

298
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:40,920
<i>When will you accept?</i>

299
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:44,640
<i>When will you know?</i>

300
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:47,280
<i>If you already have a love</i>

301
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:51,520
<i>Please, hurry and tell me</i>

302
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:54,080
<i>If you're still single</i>

303
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:57,960
<i>I beg you, with kindness</i>

304
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:03,120
<i>Take a little time to consider my heart</i>

305
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:37,080
We've arranged with Teacher Mueangphrai.

306
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,480
Then let's go.

307
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:43,520
No. If we go together,
we'll draw attention.

308
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,600
It's better if you sneak in alone.

309
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:49,760
Once you're done,
I'll find a safe spot for you to hide.

310
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,520
Okay.

311
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,120
We've arranged to meet
Village Head Prueng here.

312
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,680
Right, but where is he?

313
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:21,640
I'm here.

314
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:24,160
-Hello, Village Head.
-Yes.

315
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:28,520
They've set up guards over there.

316
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:33,040
Thank you, Village Head. Let's go.

317
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,280
Captain, I'm counting on you.

318
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,560
Make sure to take them down completely.

319
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,600
Yes.

320
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,400
-Let's go.
-Go.

321
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:55,400
<i>When will you accept?</i>

322
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:58,640
<i>When will you know?</i>

323
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:01,240
<i>If you already have a love</i>

324
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:05,920
<i>Please, hurry and tell me</i>

325
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,640
<i>If you're still single</i>

326
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:11,440
<i>I beg you, with kindness</i>

327
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:14,960
<i>Take a little time</i>

328
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:19,360
<i>To consider my heart</i>

329
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:21,960
<i>I offer you my heart</i>

330
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:25,160
<i>Waiting for your answer</i>

331
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:28,440
<i>I'm ready for you to test it</i>

332
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:33,240
<i>Inside the chamber of my heart</i>

333
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:36,000
<i>If you still see</i>

334
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:38,800
<i>The value in my goodness</i>

335
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:42,080
<i>I'm ready to give my life</i>

336
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:47,840
<i>If you consider it</i>

337
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:05,480
Our bride and groom are adorable!
Let's give them another round of applause!

338
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,000
Thank you.

339
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:13,080
Now, I'd like to invite Kamnan Pong
to the stage

340
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:15,280
to place the garlands
on our bride and groom.

341
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:42,320
Next, let's hear a few words
from Kamnan Pong for our couple.

342
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:47,400
Today is a special day.

343
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:50,040
These two feel like
my own niece and nephew.

344
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:52,880
I want to wish them both

345
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:55,240
lots of happiness together.

346
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:58,760
Forgive each other's little mistakes
along the way.

347
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:01,080
Thank you.

348
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:15,480
Maria!

349
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,640
I've got it, Teacher.

350
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,760
The tape's been converted
onto this flash drive.

351
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:27,880
Thank you so much.

352
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,320
I'll head off now.

353
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:32,600
Maria!

354
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,280
Thank you so much.

355
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:42,200
You're welcome, Teacher.

356
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,600
And now it's time

357
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,960
to hear the story

358
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:56,600
of our bride and groom.

359
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,760
I've heard that our groom

360
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,280
loves and respects his father very much.

361
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:05,680
Oh, absolutely! I love and respect my dad.

362
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:07,560
Ever since I can remember,

363
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:11,320
my dad has been a very famous singer.

364
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:14,120
But perhaps

365
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:17,040
because of the times back then,
fan culture

366
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:22,680
wasn't as open-minded as it is today.
So I couldn't reveal

367
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:25,240
that I was the son of Singha Darathong.

368
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:29,840
Even though we were apart,

369
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:32,880
I could always feel his love.

370
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,680
My father worked hard

371
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:37,960
to provide for my mom and me,

372
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,560
so we could have a good life.

373
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:45,200
One day, I moved in with him

374
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,840
because my mom had passed away.

375
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:50,440
So I had the chance to witness

376
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,960
my dad's growth.

377
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:55,840
He started as a singer, then became

378
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:59,280
a businessman, a music label executive.

379
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:02,720
He manages a label for Uncle Kamnan.

380
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:05,440
And my dad
has many other businesses as well.

381
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:07,400
That's why

382
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:10,720
I love and respect him so much.

383
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:14,440
Let's give a round of applause
for our groom!

384
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:20,560
Now it's the bride's turn.

385
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:24,800
How do you feel about the groom's father?

386
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:50,640
Anyone would love their father.

387
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,480
It's not wrong

388
00:33:55,360 --> 00:33:57,680
that Mr. Sonrak loves his dad.

389
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:06,400
But it is wrong
to let that love ignore what's right.

390
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,199
Are you sure…

391
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,040
that your father

392
00:34:23,239 --> 00:34:26,080
has lived up
to being worthy of admiration?

393
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:34,560
How dare you say that.
Take back your words right now, Puna.

394
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:37,360
This is our wedding.
Why are you saying things like this?

395
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:39,600
I'm telling the truth.

396
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:43,400
Today, everyone will finally see
what's really going on.

397
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:47,760
You're challenging me, aren't you?

398
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,960
Puna, don't. Puna!

399
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:57,320
Yes. I'm challenging you.

400
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:02,160
Puna. Dad, please don't fight.

401
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:03,680
It's our wedding, Dad!

402
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:04,960
I can't allow it!

403
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:09,880
If the woman who's going to be your wife
speaks against my honor like this,

404
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:13,600
tell her to kneel and apologize to me!

405
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:17,000
Puna, apologize to Dad, please.

406
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,120
No!

407
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,200
I will never apologize
to someone who breaks the law.

408
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:24,920
Stop talking nonsense!

409
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:28,720
Puna isn't talking nonsense.

410
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:42,200
What she's saying
is backed up with evidence.

411
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:46,800
What evidence? This is a wedding!

412
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:52,480
I'm not here to ruin the event, sir.

413
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:58,440
I have a warrant for the suspect's arrest.

414
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:01,640
Chaiya, you're…

415
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:06,120
Here it is.

416
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:09,960
The arrest warrant for Singha,
the mastermind of drug trafficking,

417
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,480
is now in my hands.

418
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:18,080
If you want to stop me from doing my job,

419
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,840
go ahead.

420
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:25,040
Your official career will end sooner.

421
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:29,400
That's not true. You're slandering my dad!

422
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:36,240
Stop turning a blind eye
and accept the truth, Mr. Sonrak.

423
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:40,200
Your father hasn't just started
dealing drugs.

424
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:42,600
He's been collaborating with Kitti

425
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,680
in drug trafficking for over 20 years.

426
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:48,320
That's not true! No way!
I don't believe it!

427
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:51,400
You're accusing my dad. There's no proof!

428
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,600
Mr. Sonrak,

429
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:55,240
if you want to see the evidence, you can.

430
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:58,640
It's all on the screen.

431
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,640
<i>About what we were talking about just now,</i>

432
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:11,920
<i>I'm sure Phupha heard us.</i>

433
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:16,640
-<i>He must know we're dealing drugs.</i>
-<i>We can't let him live, Kitti.</i>

434
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:19,760
-<i>I'll take care of it myself.</i>
-<i>How are you going to handle it?</i>

435
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,280
<i>With this gun.</i>

436
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,560
What's going on?

437
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,600
<i>Don't let it lead back to us.</i>

438
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:37,440
<i>How about this? Send Chart to his house.</i>

439
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:41,880
-<i>Make it look like an accident, okay?</i>
-<i>Yeah, good.</i>

440
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:47,120
<i>I'll handle Phupha myself.</i>

441
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:51,440
<i>Phupha, you're dead.</i>

442
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:54,560
-<i>Whoa!</i>
-<i>What's going on?</i>

443
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,440
<i>What are you doing in here?</i>

444
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,920
Besides drug trafficking,

445
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:05,240
Singha and Kitti

446
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:08,240
are the ones behind the plan
to kill my parents.

447
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,080
That's right.

448
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:23,600
You've been misleading everyone
about Onanong and Phupha all this time.

449
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:26,920
You're truly evil.
You're despicable, do you know that?

450
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:29,680
-Kamnan.
-You're evil!

451
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:41,080
Everyone is going to destroy
everything I have.

452
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,160
You're dead!

453
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,480
Dad, no!

454
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:04,480
Sonrak!

455
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:09,760
Sonrak! Why did you do this?!

456
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:13,200
Sonrak!

457
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:20,680
Sonrak! Sonrak!

458
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:24,480
Come on. Get up!

459
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:35,720
You bastards.

460
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:38,560
You did this to my son, right?

461
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:42,600
Puna! Just die already!

462
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:49,040
Let go! Let me go!

463
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:50,880
-Sonrak!
-We should go.

464
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,520
-Let go!
-Get Sonrak to the hospital.

465
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:55,600
Sonrak! Let me go!

466
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,720
-Take him!
-Sonrak!

467
00:39:57,800 --> 00:39:59,720
Let me go! Sonrak!

468
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:00,800
Come here.

469
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:04,520
I'm sorry! Sonrak!

470
00:40:05,560 --> 00:40:06,920
Let go!

471
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:15,120
What? Police storming the wedding?

472
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:18,040
Got it. I'll handle this.

473
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:19,640
PUNA & SONRAK, TARAGRAND HOTEL

474
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:23,480
Hey, get to cover and wait for orders.

475
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:37,120
-Are you okay, Puna?
-Yes, Teacher.

476
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:55,320
Teacher, do you hear that?
Who's playing Mom's song?

477
00:40:56,640 --> 00:40:57,960
I'm the one who had it played.

478
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:08,480
Go up on stage and sing this.

479
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:13,320
And you'll see your mother.

480
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:34,600
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

481
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:41,320
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

482
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:45,560
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

483
00:41:45,640 --> 00:41:48,760
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

484
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:54,040
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

485
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:57,720
-<i>But now…</i>
-<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

486
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:06,080
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

487
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:10,600
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

488
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:13,240
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

489
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:18,960
<i>My heart pounds</i>

490
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:24,200
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

491
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:30,520
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

492
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:35,480
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

493
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:38,120
<i>Before I knew it</i>

494
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:43,080
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

495
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:48,520
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

496
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:55,440
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

497
00:42:56,200 --> 00:43:00,000
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

498
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:03,680
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

499
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:07,360
<i>It bends on its own</i>

500
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:32,800
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

501
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:39,480
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

502
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:46,480
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>
<i>Before I knew it</i>

503
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:51,000
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

504
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:57,800
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

505
00:43:58,560 --> 00:44:04,680
<i>Why does it burn, unable to escape?</i>

506
00:44:04,760 --> 00:44:08,600
<i>Like iron softened by fire</i>

507
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:12,160
<i>Before the hammer strikes</i>

508
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:17,880
<i>It bends on its own</i>

509
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:19,320
Puna.

510
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:30,720
My child.

511
00:45:34,280 --> 00:45:36,080
Mom.

512
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:33,720
He's Phupha, your father.

513
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:39,560
If you and my dad had switched places,

514
00:46:39,640 --> 00:46:41,440
maybe that would've been better.

515
00:46:42,360 --> 00:46:43,960
Then you'd be my dad.

516
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:48,440
I'd finally have a father.

517
00:46:51,200 --> 00:46:52,360
Dad.

518
00:47:06,280 --> 00:47:07,960
My child.

519
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:18,560
Puna.

520
00:47:21,200 --> 00:47:24,000
-Our child.
-Yes, On.

521
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:04,240
Distinguished guests.

522
00:48:11,160 --> 00:48:14,920
I sincerely thank you all
from the bottom of my heart

523
00:48:16,880 --> 00:48:21,400
for being here to witness

524
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:24,040
justice being restored

525
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:30,440
for my dad

526
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:36,000
and my mom.

527
00:48:42,040 --> 00:48:45,040
Finally, I'd like to say…

528
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:50,760
I now have a dad and a mom!

529
00:49:01,560 --> 00:49:02,480
Mom.

530
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:05,320
Dad.

531
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:39,680
I'm happy for you, Puna.

532
00:49:54,720 --> 00:49:56,760
How could you do this to me, Kamnan?!

533
00:49:56,840 --> 00:49:58,800
Do you know how much
their parents are suffering

534
00:49:58,880 --> 00:50:00,880
seeing their child addicted to drugs?

535
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:03,280
Please go ahead, Officer.

536
00:50:03,360 --> 00:50:05,440
Don't do this, Chaiya!

537
00:50:05,520 --> 00:50:07,000
What I want most

538
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:09,360
is to see you safe.

539
00:50:09,440 --> 00:50:12,080
Hell's waiting for you, Chaiya!

540
00:50:12,160 --> 00:50:16,320
NEXT EPISODE

541
00:52:17,920 --> 00:52:20,760
